id: pm-c1bn
title: Fix pm test run exit semantics for failed linked tests
description: Ensure pm test --run returns dependency-failed exit status when any linked test run result is failed.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: exit-codes,external-audit,linked-tests,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-04-04T18:16:15.038Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-05T17:57:21.389Z"
deadline: "2026-04-14T18:16:15.038Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: pm test --run returns exit code 5 when any run_results entry has status failed; integration and runtime tests cover the behavior; docs/contracts are updated.
definition_of_ready: Repro commands and target files are linked before implementation starts.
order: 3
goal: Linked-test reliability
objective: Guarantee CI-safe exit semantics for pm test --run
value: Prevents false-green automation when linked tests fail
impact: Improves trust in linked-test evidence and gating
outcome: pm test command exits non-zero on linked-test failures
why_now: Current behavior can silently bypass failure gates in automation.
parent: pm-5z9r
reviewer: maintainer-review
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: external-audit-followup
release: vnext
reporter: codex-agent
severity: high
environment: linux
repro_steps: Run pm test <id> --run with fail-on-context-mismatch and observe failed run_results with process exit code 0.
resolution: Implemented linked-test empty-run strict guardrails and failure categorization.
expected_result: Strict mode should fail successful-empty test selections to avoid false confidence.
actual_result: "Added --fail-on-empty-test-run to test/test-all with pattern detection and empty_run reporting, validated by tests."
affected_version: 2026.3.12
fixed_version: target-vnext
component: linked-test-runtime
regression: true
customer_impact: CI and scripts may proceed despite known linked-test failures.
